zes the experiences of academically talented Black undergraduate women navigating their social and academic lives at urban historically white institutions and offers strategies for creating more inclusive academic and social environments for talented undergraduates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAfrican American college studentsxSocial conditions. 0aAfrican American womenxEducation (Higher) 0aDiscrimination in higher educationzUnited States. 0aGifted womenxInterviews. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197883241140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978832411423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978832411/original  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK